The paper deals with the planar embedding conjecture, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves metric embeddings, which is a topic in Discrete Mathematics, and hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as the planar embedding conjecture has implications in game theory. The paper involves curvature, which is a topic in Differential Geometry, and hence cs.MG (Mathematical Physics) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves constant-distortion embeddings, which is a topic in Information Theory, and hence cs.IT (Information Theory) may also be a relevant sub-category.
